    "summary": "Skilled in Corporate & Trade Financing, passionate about financial markets, I hold an MBA in Private Banking & Investments, a BSc in Science & Technology and an Associate Degree in International Trade, with an overall 7 years of experience in large multinational financial institutions as Corporate Banking Associate, including 1 year as Banker/Relationship Manager growing the credit portfolio by ~USD 80 million within that time frame. \n\n> I am a curious and resourceful multilingual professional (English, Portuguese, French, and Spanish), organized, hands-on with an analytic perspective and ownership posture. I consistently work well under pressure with tight deadlines led by revenue origination goals.\n> Demonstrated strengths within key areas of Corporate Banking such as Trade Finance, Working Capital, Capital Markets debt issuances and Derivatives/FX products. \n> Positions held at the front line of multinational banks had enhanced my Problem Solving and Interpersonal skills. Also, I am currently studying for the CFA Level I exam.\n> Since the beginning of my career as an intern, I have been considered a consistently high performer worker in all of my positions with strong potential, which definitely led to a considerably high career growth rate, managing my own large customers portfolio by 26 years old.\n\nA professional currently responsible for the daily coverage of large credit customers (over R$ 1 billion annual revenues), origination of new deals, focusing on financial credit analysis, customer service and coordination of each deal flow. \n\nWith a keen interest in international cultures & languages, I have done two exchange programs to Canada, firstly to Montreal for 2 months to learn French and then to Toronto for 6 months to master the business English fluency. Apart from those experiences, I have travelled to South America and Europe on my free time while working for two Asian multinational banks, MUFG (largest bank in Japan) and ICBC (largest bank in China), preparing myself to be a \u201cglobal citizen\u201d.\n\n\u2714 European Citizenship",
